{
  "texts": [
    "(Schulman et al., 2017) GAE is a variance reduction scheme for policy gradients that adapts the advantage estimation function.",
    "With an adapted advantage estimation function, variance is significantly reduced while the introduced bias is kept as low as possible.",
    "(Schulman et al. 2015) Value normalization has been empirically proven to positively affect the performance of PPO training in MARL settings.",
    "(Yu et al., 2021) The benefit of advantage normalization for PG methods was shown by Gruslys et al. (2017) Moreover, input normalization, which was proven to improve convergence (LeCun et al., 2012), is used before passing data to the NNs.",
    "Active masks are used to denote inactive agents."
  ]
}